03051nmm a2200481Ia 9780520353886DE-B159720240326120151.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240326t19981998cau    fo  d z      eng d  a97805203538867 a10.1525/97805203538862doi  a(DE-B1597)649389  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  acaucUS-CA 7aSOC0320002bisacsh1 aGarrow, David J, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aLiberty and Sexuality :bThe Right to Privacy and the Making of ‹i›Roe v. Wade‹/i›, Updated /cDavid J Garrow; ed. by David J. Garrow. 1aBerkeley, CA : bUniversity of California Press, c[1998] 4c©1998  a1 online resource (1064 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aLiberty and Sexuality is a definitive account of the legal and political struggles that created the right to privacy and won constitutional protection for a woman's right to choose abortion.Roe v. Wade, the landmark 1973 U.S. Supreme Court ruling that established that right, grew out of not only efforts to legalize abortion but also out of earlier battles against statutes that criminalized birth control. When the U.S. Supreme Court in 1965, in Griswold v. Connecticut, voided such a prohibition as an outrageous intrusion upon marital privacy, it opened a previously unimagined constitutional door: the opportunity to argue that a woman's access to a safe, legal abortion was also a fundamental constitutional right.Garrow's essential history details both the unheralded contributions of the young lawyers who filed America's first abortion rights cases and also the inside-the-Supreme Court deliberations that produced Roe v. Wade.In this updated and expanded paperback edition, Garrow also traces the post-Roe evolution of abortion rights battles and the wider struggle for sexual privacy up through the 25th anniversary of Roe in early 1998.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aGender Studies. 4aSocial Science. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh1 aGarrow, David J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt0 cprintz978052021302940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052035388640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520353886423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520353886/original  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles